title%22%3A%22The%20US%20military%20is%20falling%20behind%20in%20the%20race%20to%20field%20combat%20drones%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%221249%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Defense%20Secretary%20Pete%20Hegseth%20hosted%20a%20drone%20demonstration%20at%20the%20Pentagon.%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F68c1e80ff9db348adc0b3df6%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%221873%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EDefense%20Secretary%20Pete%20Hegseth%20hosted%20a%20drone%20demonstration%20at%20the%20Pentagon%20on%20July%2010%2C%202025.%3Cp%3ELance%20Cpl.%20Isaac%20Llanez%20Delgado%2FUS%20Marine%20Corps%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3EThis%20story%20originally%20appeared%20in%20Politico%20Magazine%20and%20appears%20on%20Business%20Insider%20through%20the%20Axel%20Springer%20Global%20Network.%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWhen%20the%20Pentagon%20announced%20a%20%26quot%3Bjoint%20interagency%20task%20force%26quot%3B%20in%20July%20to%20bring%20the%20US%20military%20up%20to%20speed%20on%20drone%20warfare%2C%20Vice%20Chief%20of%20Staff%20of%20the%20Army%20Gen.%20James%20Mingus%20compared%20drones%20to%20the%20threat%20of%20improvised%20explosive%20devices%20two%20decades%20earlier%20in%20Iraq.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20drone%2C%20said%20Mingus%2C%20%26quot%3Bis%20our%20IED%20of%20today%26quot%3B%20%E2%80%94%20a%20war-transforming%20technology%20that%20smaller%20powers%20could%20use%20to%20put%20big%20powers%20at%20a%20disadvantage.%20Ukraine%20has%20demonstrated%20this%20brilliantly%20over%20the%20last%20few%20years%20through%20its%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fukraine-drone-defense-tech-industry-warfare-russia-attacks-2025-4%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Einnovative%20use%20of%20drones%3C%2Fa%3E%20to%20stymie%20the%20invading%20Russians.%20And%2020-odd%20years%20ago%2C%20another%20nation%20that%20once%20saw%20itself%20as%20all-powerful%20on%20the%20battlefield%20%E2%80%94%20the%20United%20States%20%E2%80%94%20found%20itself%20flummoxed%20in%20the%20streets%20of%20Iraq%20and%20Afghanistan%20as%20insurgents%20deployed%20IEDs%20to%20kill%20or%20maim%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwarontherocks.com%2F2017%2F05%2Fhow-the-ied-won-dispelling-the-myth-of-tactical-success-and-innovation%2F%23%3A~%3Atext%3DWhether%2520you%2520measure%2520in%2520blood%2Cof%2520veteran%2520and%2520Afghan%2520amputees.%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ethousands%20of%20young%20Americans%3C%2Fa%3E%20in%20a%20new%20kind%20of%20%26quot%3Basymmetric%26quot%3B%20warfare.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BWe%20cannot%20move%20fast%20enough%20in%20this%20space%2C%26quot%3B%20Mingus%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.csis.org%2Fanalysis%2Fstrategic-landpower-dialogue-conversation-vcsa-general-james-mingus%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Esaid%20last%20month%3C%2Fa%3E.%20What%20he%20neglected%20to%20say%2C%20however%2C%20was%20that%20the%20Pentagon%20took%20tragically%20long%20to%20combat%20the%20IED.%20Many%20within%20the%20military%20and%20Congress%20%E2%80%94%20among%20them%2C%20notably%2C%20then-Sen.%20Joe%20Biden%20%E2%80%94%20were%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.presidency.ucsb.edu%2Fdocuments%2Fstatement-senator-joe-biden-mrap-delivery-delay-unacceptable-and-will-cost-lives%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eoutraged%20over%3C%2Fa%3E%20nearly%20two%20years%20of%20delays%20in%20deploying%20the%20MRAP%2C%20or%20%26quot%3BMine%20Resistant%20Ambush%20Protected%26quot%3B%20vehicle%2C%20to%20address%20the%20IED%20threat.%20The%20issue%20wasn't%20resolved%20until%20a%20new%20defense%20secretary%2C%20Robert%20Gates%2C%20took%20over%20for%20Donald%20Rumsfeld%20in%202006.%20Appalled%20by%20what%20he%20called%20daily%20%26quot%3Bfuneral%20pyres%20for%20our%20troops%2C%26quot%3B%20Gates%20imposed%20his%20will%20over%20bureaucratic%20resistance%20from%20the%20Pentagon%20%E2%80%94%20%26quot%3BHurry%20up!%20Troops%20are%20dying%2C%26quot%3B%20he'd%20tell%20reluctant%20officials%20over%20and%20over%20%E2%80%94%20and%20launched%20a%20crash%20program%20to%20send%20thousands%20of%20MRAPS%20to%20Iraq%20and%20Afghanistan.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%222000%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22A%20Ukrainian%20soldier%20loads%20ammunition%20onto%20a%20drone%20at%20a%20training%20in%20September.%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F68c1a9ed57d362d375e7e705%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%221333%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EA%20Ukrainian%20soldier%20loads%20ammunition%20onto%20a%20drone%20at%20a%20training%20in%20September.%3Cp%3EDiego%20Herrera%20Carcedo%2FAnadolu%20via%20Getty%20Images%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3ECritics%20say%20the%20Defense%20Department%20is%20having%20similar%20problems%20now%20with%20drones.%20In%20that%20earlier%20era%2C%20as%20Gates%20wrote%20in%20his%202014%20memoir%2C%20%26quot%3BDuty%3A%20Memoirs%20of%20a%20Secretary%20at%20War%2C%26quot%3B%20the%20long%20delays%20in%20deploying%20the%20MRAP%20occurred%20because%20%26quot%3Bno%20one%20at%20a%20senior%20level%20wanted%20to%20spend%20the%20money%20to%20buy%20them%26quot%3B%20and%20officials%20in%20the%20Pentagon's%20%26quot%3Bhidebound%20and%20unresponsive%20bureaucratic%20structure%20%E2%80%A6%20were%20wed%20to%20their%20old%20plans%2C%20programs%20and%20thinking.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EToday%2C%20some%20military%20experts%20say%20that%2C%20for%20many%20of%20the%20same%20bureaucratic%20reasons%2C%20the%20Pentagon%20has%20been%20far%20too%20slow%20to%20adapt%20to%20the%20latest%20evolution%20in%20asymmetric%20warfare%3A%20drones.%20Indeed%2C%20much%20of%20the%20catch-up%20has%20occurred%20only%20in%20the%20last%20month%20or%20so.%20Shortly%20after%20the%20task%20force%20was%20announced%20in%20July%2C%20Defense%20Secretary%20Pete%20Hegseth%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.documentcloud.org%2Fdocuments%2F25995487-250710-dod-memo-unleashing-us-military-drone-dominance%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eunveiled%20a%20major%20initiative%3C%2Fa%3E%20called%20%26quot%3BUnleashing%20US%20Military%20Drone%20Dominance%2C%26quot%3B%20and%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.defense.gov%2FNews%2FNews-Stories%2FArticle%2FArticle%2F4246987%2Fpentagon-to-increase-low-cost-drone-production-in-us%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Edeclared%20at%3C%2Fa%3E%20a%20news%20conference%20that%20%26quot%3Bdrones%20are%20the%20biggest%20battlefield%20innovation%20in%20a%20generation.%26quot%3B%20However%2C%20Hegseth%20noted%20offhandedly%2C%20to%20date%20%26quot%3BUS%20units%20are%20not%20outfitted%20with%20the%20lethal%20small%20drones%20the%20modern%20battlefield%20requires.%26quot%3B%20He%20mostly%20blamed%20the%20Biden%20administration%20for%20the%20delays%2C%20saying%20it%20only%20%26quot%3Bdeployed%20red%20tape%26quot%3B%20while%20%26quot%3Bour%20adversaries%20collectively%20produce%20millions%20of%20cheap%20drones%20each%20year.%26quot%3B%20(The%20Pentagon%20did%20not%20respond%20to%20requests%20for%20comment.)%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMost%20significantly%2C%20after%20watching%20Ukrainians%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fukrainian-drones-use-fire-spewing-ammo-ensure-russian-tanks-destroyed-2025-3%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Edestroy%3C%2Fa%3E%20Russian%20tanks%20and%20strategic%20aircraft%20with%20armed%20drones%2C%20Hegseth%20said%20drones%20should%20now%20be%20treated%20like%20munitions%20%E2%80%94%20cheap%2C%20expendable%2C%20and%20mass%20producible%20%E2%80%94%20and%20not%20like%20a%20new%2C%20expensive%20aircraft%2C%20development%20of%20which%20can%20take%20years%20longer%20to%20get%20through%20Pentagon%20red%20tape.%20The%20DoD's%20new%20drone%20policy%20also%20seeks%20to%20expedite%20drone%20use%20by%20giving%20lower-level%20commanders%20%E2%80%94%20basically%20colonels%20in%20the%20US%20Army%2C%20US%20Marine%20Corps%2C%20and%20the%20US%20Air%20Force%2C%20and%20captains%20in%20the%20US%20Navy%20%E2%80%94%20authority%20to%20purchase%20and%20deploy%20so-called%20Group%201%20and%202%20drones%2C%20or%20smaller%20vehicles%20like%20tiny%20FPV%20(for%20%26quot%3Bfirst%20person%20view%26quot%3B)%20quadcopters%20that%20can%20be%20used%20at%20the%20unit%20level%20and%20have%20been%20so%20effective%20on%20the%20front%20lines%20of%20the%20Russia-Ukraine%20conflict.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%221777%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Defense%20Secretary%20Pete%20Hegseth%20held%20a%20Dronebuster%20jammer%20in%20February.%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F68c1edc832af4d666ef7a9a1%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%221333%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EDefense%20Secretary%20Pete%20Hegseth%20held%20a%20Dronebuster%20jammer%20in%20February.%3Cp%3EPetty%20Officer%201st%20Class%20Alexander%20C.%20Kubitza%2FDefense%20Department%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EAll%20of%20that%20amounts%20to%20a%20good%20start%2C%20critics%20say.%20But%20that%20is%20also%20the%20problem%3A%20The%20Defense%20Department%20is%20just%20getting%20started%2C%20as%20even%20Mingus%20has%20admitted.%20By%20the%20accounts%20of%20many%20experts%2C%20the%20US%20military%20is%20not%20close%20to%20developing%2C%20much%20less%20deploying%2C%20the%20dizzying%20array%20of%20sophisticated%20drones%20mastered%20by%20the%20Ukrainians%20and%20Russians%20%E2%80%94%20including%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Frussia-struggling-with-ukraine-cessna-style-drone-flying-brick-bomb-2024-5%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3E%26quot%3Bkamikaze%26quot%3B%20drones%3C%2Fa%3E%20used%20to%20destroy%20enemy%20tanks%20and%20vehicles%3B%20ground%20drones%20that%20can%20lay%20mines%20and%20deliver%20ammunition%20and%20medicine%3B%20larger%20drones%20that%20can%20ferry%20smaller%20ones%20behind%20enemy%20lines%2C%20among%20others.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThere's%20a%20lot%20of%20talky-talky%20and%20not%20a%20lot%20of%20showy-showy%2C%26quot%3B%20says%20Benjamin%20Jensen%2C%20a%20reserve%20U