0part%20because%20it%20was%20started%20under%20Trump's%20predecessor%2C%20Joe%20Biden%2C%20many%20experts%20believe.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBut%20even%20the%20Biden%20administration%20slow-walked%20that%20program.%20The%20Pentagon%20spends%20tens%20of%20billions%20of%20dollars%20annually%20sustaining%20and%20upgrading%20aircraft%20carriers%2C%20F-35%20jets%20and%20tanks%2C%20but%20it%20budgeted%20only%20%24500%20million%20for%20low-cost%20drones%20%E2%80%94%20just%200.05%25%20of%20the%20Pentagon%20budget%20%E2%80%94%20through%20the%20first%20round%20of%20its%20signature%20Replicator%20Initiative%20in%202023%2C%20says%20Michael%20Horowitz%2C%20who%20as%20deputy%20assistant%20secretary%20of%20defense%20for%20force%20development%20in%20the%20Biden%20administration%20was%20one%20of%20the%20originators%20of%20Replicator.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThe%20Russia-Ukraine%20war%20demonstrated%20in%20practice%20what%20a%20lot%20of%20people%2C%20including%20myself%2C%20had%20been%20saying%20in%20theory%20about%20the%20way%20that%20robotics%20and%20AI%20would%20shape%20the%20future%20character%20of%20war%2C%26quot%3B%20Horowitz%20says.%20%26quot%3BThese%20kinds%20of%20strike%20capabilities%20are%20becoming%20a%20ubiquitous%20part%20of%20warfare%2C%20an%20essential%20capability%20that%20every%20military%20needs%20to%20deploy.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Chr%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%222000%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22The%20moment%20of%20impact%20as%20seen%20from%20Ukraine's%20Vampire%20heavy%20bomber%20drone.%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F68c1ba14f9db348adc0b384d%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%221333%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EThe%20moment%20of%20impact%20as%20seen%20from%20Ukraine's%20Vampire%20heavy%20bomber%20drone.%3Cp%3EUkrinform%2FNurPhoto%20via%20Getty%20Images%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3ENo%20one%2C%20of%20course%2C%20is%20going%20to%20win%20a%20war%20with%20drones%20alone.%20%26quot%3BThe%20Ukrainians%20are%20not%20going%20to%20be%20able%20to%20take%20back%20Crimea%20or%20parts%20of%20the%20Donbas%20with%20drones%20or%20autonomous%20attritable%20vehicles%2C%26quot%3B%20says%20Nadia%20Schadlow%2C%20a%20senior%20fellow%20at%20the%20Hudson%20Institute%20who%20served%20as%20deputy%20national%20security%20adviser%20for%20strategy%20in%20the%20first%20Trump%20administration.%20%26quot%3BThe%20key%20will%20be%20which%20militaries%20can%20adapt%20to%20combining%20autonomy%20with%20other%20platforms%20and%20operational%20concepts.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BDrones%20aren't%20really%20all%20that%20technologically%20advanced%2C%26quot%3B%20adds%20retired%20Col.%20Anthony%20Pfaff%2C%20director%20of%20the%20Strategic%20Studies%20Institute%20at%20the%20US%20Army%20War%20College.%20%26quot%3BHowever%2C%20they%20have%20an%20attribute%20that%20nothing%20else%20on%20the%20battlefield%20does.%20They're%20really%20cheap%2C%20so%20weaker%20actors%20can%20buy%20them%20by%20the%20millions.%20It%20allows%20the%20weaker%20actor%20to%20lessen%20the%20risk%20to%20his%20own%20forces%20while%20increasing%20it%20to%20the%20enemy.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAnd%20as%20security%20specialist%20Joyce%20Hakmeh%20put%20it%20in%20a%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.chathamhouse.org%2F2025%2F03%2Fwhat-ukraine-can-teach-europe-and-world-about-innovation-modern-warfare%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Erecent%20Chatham%20House%20report%3C%2Fa%3E%3A%20%26quot%3BUkraine's%20advantage%20has%20not%20been%20in%20the%20individual%20technologies%20it%20has%20deployed%2C%20but%20in%20its%20ability%20to%20regularly%20outpace%20Russia%20in%20the%20innovation%20cycle.%20It%20is%20a%20model%20that%20other%20countries%20must%20study%20if%20they%20hope%20to%20maintain%20military%20readiness%20in%20the%2021st%20century.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EYet%20the%20Pentagon%20hasn't%20quite%20figured%20out%20who%20is%20in%20charge%20of%20this%20major%20transformation%20in%20asymmetric%20warfare%2C%20what%20some%20call%2